36#include "gsskrb5_locl.h"
37
38OM_uint32 GSSAPI_CALLCONV _gsskrb5_export_name
39 (OM_uint32 * minor_status,
40 gss_const_name_t input_name,
41 gss_buffer_t exported_name
42 )
43{
44 krb5_context context;
45 krb5_const_principal princ = (krb5_const_principal)input_name;
46 krb5_error_code kret;
47 char *buf, *name;
48 size_t len;
49
50 GSSAPI_KRB5_INIT (&context);
51
52 kret = krb5_unparse_name (context, princ, &name);
53 if (kret) {
54 *minor_status = kret;
55 return GSS_S_FAILURE;
56 }
57 len = strlen (name);
58
59 exported_name->length = 10 + len + GSS_KRB5_MECHANISM->length;
60 exported_name->value = malloc(exported_name->length);
61 if (exported_name->value == NULL) {
62 free (name);
63 *minor_status = ENOMEM;
64 return GSS_S_FAILURE;
65 }
66
67 /* TOK, MECH_OID_LEN, DER(MECH_OID), NAME_LEN, NAME */
68
69 buf = exported_name->value;
70 memcpy(buf, "\x04\x01", 2);
71 buf += 2;
72 buf[0] = ((GSS_KRB5_MECHANISM->length + 2) >> 8) & 0xff;
73 buf[1] = (GSS_KRB5_MECHANISM->length + 2) & 0xff;
74 buf+= 2;
75 buf[0] = 0x06;
76 buf[1] = (GSS_KRB5_MECHANISM->length) & 0xFF;
77 buf+= 2;
78
79 memcpy(buf, GSS_KRB5_MECHANISM->elements, GSS_KRB5_MECHANISM->length);
80 buf += GSS_KRB5_MECHANISM->length;
81
82 buf[0] = (len >> 24) & 0xff;
83 buf[1] = (len >> 16) & 0xff;
84 buf[2] = (len >> 8) & 0xff;
85 buf[3] = (len) & 0xff;
86 buf += 4;
87
88 memcpy (buf, name, len);
89
90 free (name);
91
92 *minor_status = 0;
93 return GSS_S_COMPLETE;
94}
